main event: A civilian reported observing an unidentified object in Kettering, Ohio on December 16, 1966 for 15 minutes.
interesting points: The observation lasted 15 minutes and was confirmed to be visual from the ground., The witness filled out a Project Blue Book form detailing the event., The object was visualized as being pink and larger around., The witness used various means (eyeglasses, binoculars) to observe the object., There were weather conditions recorded at the time, indicating it was cloudy.
